'''阿爾-古拉巴墓地'''（{{lang-en|Al-Ghuraba cemetery}}）是位於黎巴嫩北黎巴嫩省[[的黎波里_(黎巴嫩)|的黎波里]]的[[公墓|公墓]]，曾用於集體埋葬因[[黎巴嫩內戰|黎巴嫩內戰]]和[[2007年黎巴嫩武裝衝突|2007年黎巴嫩武裝衝突]]而死亡的遺體。自1970年代以來，該墓地長期被若干臨時房屋占用，在2010年時約有1,000人居住於該地。2015年，{{tsl|en|Care International|國際關懷協會}}報告顯示該墓地的居住條件極差。

== 安葬 ==
阿爾-古拉巴墓地位於[[的黎波里_(黎巴嫩)|的黎波里]]的巴布艾特巴尼（Bab-al-Tibbaneh）和賈巴穆森（Jabal Mohsen）社區附近<ref name=care29/>，「阿爾-古拉巴（Al-Ghuraba）」在[[黎巴嫩阿拉伯語|黎巴嫩阿拉伯語]]中意為「陌生人」。<ref name=lau/>

該墓地曾被用於集體安葬在衝突中喪生的人。[[國際特赦組織|國際特赦組織]]於1989年的報告中指出，1986年12月21和22日在Bab-al-Tibbaneh社區有多達200名遇害的男子、婦女和兒童埋葬於[[推土機|推土機]]挖掘的[[亂葬崗|亂葬崗]]中，其中一部分是在[[黎巴嫩內戰|黎巴嫩內戰]]期間喪生的平民，另有部分據稱是被[[敘利亞軍隊|敘利亞軍隊]]及其盟友處決的[[遜尼派|遜尼派]][[穆斯林|穆斯林]]。<ref>{{cite book |last1=United States Congress House Committee on Foreign Affairs Subcommittee on Europe and the Middle East |title=The Situation in Lebanon, July 1989: Hearing Before the Subcommittee on Europe and the Middle East of the Committee on Foreign Affairs, House of Representatives, One Hundred First Congress, First Session, July 25, 1989 |year=1989 |publisher=U.S. Government Printing Office |page=149 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=h-l8pznU9tYC |language=en}}</ref>2007年10月4日，黎巴嫩政府將約98具遺體埋葬在該墓地中，是[[2007年黎巴嫩武裝衝突|2007年黎巴嫩武裝衝突]]期間喪生又無人認領的{{tsl|en|Fatah al-Islam|伊斯蘭法塔組織}}成員遺體。<ref>{{cite news |title=Fatah al-Islam terrorists buried in north Lebanon |url=http://twocircles.net/2007oct04/fatah_al_islam_terrorists_buried_north_lebanon.html |accessdate=2020-10-22 |work=TwoCircles |publisher=新華社 |date=2007-10-05 |language=en |archive-date=2020-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026084320/http://twocircles.net/2007oct04/fatah_al_islam_terrorists_buried_north_lebanon.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Zaatari |first1=Mohammed |title=Government buries 98 Fatah al-Islam militants |url=https://www.dailystar.com.lb/ArticlePrint.aspx?id=46831&mode=print |accessdate=2020-10-22 |work=The Daily Star Newspaper - Lebanon |date=2007-10-05 |language=en |archive-date=2020-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026133334/https://www.dailystar.com.lb/ArticlePrint.aspx?id=46831&mode=print |dead-url=no }}</ref>

== 居民 ==
的黎波里於1970和80年代湧入大量低收入戶，由於缺乏適當的房屋，許多人選擇定居於阿爾-古拉巴墓地。<ref name=iwpr>{{cite news |last1=Al-Ali |first1=Amani |title=Growing Up in a Graveyard |url=https://iwpr.net/global-voices/growing-graveyard |accessdate=2020-10-22 |work=Institute for War and Peace Reporting |date=2011-01-26 |language=en |archive-date=2020-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026041038/https://iwpr.net/global-voices/growing-graveyard |dead-url=no }}</ref>2010年的黎波里市政研究發現，有187個家庭約1,000人仍居住於自行搭建的臨時的房屋中<ref name=care29>{{cite book |title=Shelter Needs and the Most Vulnerable in Tripoli, Lebanon: Rapid Urban Assessment |date=2015 |publisher=CARE International UK |pages=29–30 |url=https://www.careemergencytoolkit.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/CARE_LB-Rapid-Shelter-Assessment-in-Tripoli2015.pdf |language=en |access-date=2020-11-26 |archive-date=2020-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026064456/https://www.careemergencytoolkit.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/CARE_LB-Rapid-Shelter-Assessment-in-Tripoli2015.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=iwpr/>，同時上升的[[出生率|出生率]]亦顯示人口將會增加。<ref name=iwpr/>另外，儘管在[[敘利亞內戰|敘利亞內戰]]期間有大量敘利亞難民湧入，但當地大多數居民仍為黎巴嫩裔。<ref>{{cite book |title=Shelter Needs and the Most Vulnerable in Tripoli, Lebanon: Rapid Urban Assessment |date=2015 |publisher=CARE International UK |pages=31 |url=https://www.careemergencytoolkit.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/CARE_LB-Rapid-Shelter-Assessment-in-Tripoli2015.pdf |language=en |access-date=2020-11-26 |archive-date=2020-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026064456/https://www.careemergencytoolkit.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/CARE_LB-Rapid-Shelter-Assessment-in-Tripoli2015.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>墓地的所有權大部分為國有，一部分由[[清真寺|清真寺]]{{tsl|en|Mortmain|永久保管}}，[[業主|業主]]與居民間偶爾會發生土地糾紛。<ref name=care29/>

{{tsl|en|Care International|國際關懷協會}}英國分部2015年的一份報告指出，該地的生活條件較差，其中有20％的居民的生活水平低於{{tsl|en|Sphere (organization)|環球 (組織)|環球計畫}}{{NoteTag|由[[樂施會|樂施會]]、[[國際紅十字與紅新月運動|國際紅十字與紅新月運動]]等多個國際非政府組織共同制定的人道援助最低標準。<ref>{{Cite web|title=《環球計劃－人道主義憲章與人道救援響應最低標準》的推廣工作|url=https://www.oxfam.org.hk/tc/what-we-do-category/humanitarian/sphereproject|accessdate=2020-11-26|work=香港樂施會|language=zh-hant|archive-date=2020-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201025203554/https://oxfam.org.hk/tc/what-we-do-category/humanitarian/sphereproject|dead-url=no}}</ref>}}所涵蓋的居住空間標準。<ref>{{cite book |title=Shelter Needs and the Most Vulnerable in Tripoli, Lebanon: Rapid Urban Assessment |date=2015 |publisher=CARE International UK |pages=35 |url=https://www.careemergencytoolkit.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/CARE_LB-Rapid-Shelter-Assessment-in-Tripoli2015.pdf |language=en |access-date=2020-11-26 |archive-date=2020-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026064456/https://www.careemergencytoolkit.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/CARE_LB-Rapid-Shelter-Assessment-in-Tripoli2015.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>該些房屋主要為單間的單層樓建築，且經常缺乏部分牆壁、屋頂或地基，冬季時寒冷潮濕，許多家庭也未擁有任何家具。<ref name=care29/>雖然的黎波里市政當局允許安裝部分電力供應設備，但當地的基礎設施仍然極差，[[衛生設施|衛生設施]]為開放式[[下水道|下水道]]<ref name=iwpr/><ref name=care29/>，同時有60％的廁所缺乏[[自來水|自來水]]槽，供水困難、75％的廁所未有隔間門。<ref>{{cite book |title=Shelter Needs and the Most Vulnerable in Tripoli, Lebanon: Rapid Urban Assessment |date=2015 |publisher=CARE International UK |pages=40 |url=https://www.careemergencytoolkit.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/CARE_LB-Rapid-Shelter-Assessment-in-Tripoli2015.pdf |language=en |access-date=2020-11-26 |archive-date=2020-10-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201026064456/https://www.careemergencytoolkit.org/wp-content/uploads/2017/09/CARE_LB-Rapid-Shelter-Assessment-in-Tripoli2015.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>儘管許多家庭透過協助安葬死者賺錢，並因此受到汙名化，其收入仍然很低，當地也有許多孩童並未就學。<ref name=care29/><ref name=iwpr/>市政當局已計畫改善當地的生活條件，包括在附近興建一座新的住宅區。<ref name=iwpr/>

[[巴布艾特巴尼-賈巴穆森衝突|巴布艾特巴尼-賈巴穆森衝突]]期間，該地的部分房屋被砲彈損毀。<ref name=care29/>阿爾-古拉巴墓地附近居民曾出現在2007年紀錄片《陌生人》（''The Strangers''）中。<ref name=lau>{{cite news |title=Film brings to life the forgotten stories of destitute families in North Lebanon |url=https://www.lau.edu.lb/news-events/news/archive/film_brings_to_life_the_forgot/ |accessdate=2020-10-22 |work=Lebanese American University |date=2009-01-30 |language=en |archive-date=2020-10-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201027015317/https://www.lau.edu.lb/news-events/news/archive/film_brings_to_life_the_forgot/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

